// readme file of CrossRouter source directory

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Makefile

$ make
to make a release version.
This will only output the routing result.

$ make debug
to make a debug version.
This will output detail information and generate TeX files that can be visulized
* these two files must be in the run directory
  - result_footer.tex
  - result_header.tex

$ make parser
Genearte corresponding TeX source that visualizes the benchmark.
Used with genTexFile.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

usage of executable

To run on a benchmark:
$ ./main benchmark [idx]
where [idx] is optional to run on a specific subproblem

To parse a benchmark:
$ ./parser benchmark

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Directory

- ASPDAC10_expr/
Contains test cases used in ASPDAC10 and experimentail results 

- ISPD08_case
Contains test cases used in ISPD08 (Cho's paper, high performance droplet router)

- ISPD10_expr/
Contains placement generated by our ILP-placement method, and routing results.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Script files

There are several script files for various kinds of usages.
Please modify them accordingly.

- *.tex : TeX files that used to genearte visulization of routing result
- clean.sh : clean up all the log files generated by the program
- batch : run program on a benchmark and make summary of results
- evaluate.sh : evaluate the result generated by `batch', e.g., cell used, run time
- genTexFile : Given a benchmark, generate a TeX file that visulizes all the subproblems

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

source files

descriptions of the source and header files can be found inside the files 
